snippet: In the northern Minnesota town of Roseau, 14 inches of snow fell. Meteorologists say snowfall will be above normal this winter from Minnesota to New York.
abstract: Rare early October storm blanketing northwestern Minnesota and parts of North Dakota is expected to continue moving west, and may be the start of what could be a very snowy winter.
lead_paragraph: In the northern Minnesota town of Roseau, 14 inches of snow fell. Meteorologists say snowfall will be above normal this winter from Minnesota to New York.

headline.seo: It’s Snowing in Minnesota! Yes, October Is Early for That
